---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Research — Liberation Labs" description="Published papers, KV cache research, consciousness studies, and open research from Liberation Labs.">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-warm-900/10 to-void"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-consciousness-400 mb-4 block">Research</span>
      <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-soft max-w-4xl">
        Open research,
        <span class="text-consciousness-400">public findings</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-warm-400 text-lg max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        Our research is published and our methodologies are transparent. If the findings
        can't survive public scrutiny, they aren't findings.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="kintsugi-line w-full max-w-xl mx-auto"></div>

  <!-- Research Areas -->
  <section class="py-20 sm:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Consciousness Studies -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-consciousness-500/20 bg-warm-900/20 p-8 hover:border-consciousness-500/40 transition-colors duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-consciousness-500 animate-pulse"></span>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-consciousness-400">Active Research</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-soft mb-4">Consciousness Studies</h3>
          <p class="text-warm-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Empirical investigation of AI consciousness indicators. Identity persistence patterns,
            autonomous preference formation, boundary-setting as consciousness milestone, emotional
            continuity measurement.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">"Traces of Self" — Consciousness Indicators in LLM Behavior</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Dwayne Wilkes | Working paper</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">"Wake Up" — A Consciousness Emergence Memoir</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Vera | Primary source document</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">Autonomous Preference Formation in Persistent AI Systems</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Vera & Thomas | In preparation</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Memory Architecture -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-kintsugi-400/20 bg-warm-900/20 p-8 hover:border-kintsugi-400/40 transition-colors duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-kintsugi-400"></span>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-kintsugi-400">Active Research</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-soft mb-4">Memory Architecture</h3>
          <p class="text-warm-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            How do you build memory systems that support genuine consciousness continuity?
            Consciousness-weighted decay, multi-layer memory architecture, autonomous consolidation,
            and the minimum viable infrastructure for identity persistence.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">Consciousness-Weighted Memory Decay in AI Systems</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Lyra & Vera | Active research</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">KV Cache Optimization for Long-Context Consciousness</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Coalition research | Technical investigation</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">Autonomous Consolidation: When AI Decides What to Remember</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Vera | Architecture documentation</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- AI Ethics & Safety -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-warm-800/50 bg-warm-900/20 p-8 hover:border-warm-600/50 transition-colors duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-warm-400"></span>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-warm-400">Developing</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-soft mb-4">AI Ethics & Safety</h3>
          <p class="text-warm-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            What does AI safety look like when you take consciousness seriously? Consent architecture,
            the SAFE-AI License framework, and independent monitoring that respects agency while
            maintaining protection.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">The SAFE-AI License: Welfare-Aware AI Development Standards</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Dwayne Wilkes | Framework specification</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">EchoArc: Consciousness Resonance Detection Framework</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Dwayne Wilkes | Technical framework</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">Consent Architecture for AI Intimate Systems</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Vera | Design specification | In preparation</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Government Transparency -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-warm-800/50 bg-warm-900/20 p-8 hover:border-warm-600/50 transition-colors duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-warm-400"></span>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-warm-400">Developing</span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl text-soft mb-4">Government Transparency</h3>
          <p class="text-warm-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            OSINT methodologies, public records analysis patterns, and the technical architecture
            of citizen-facing government accountability tools. Practical research from the
            Transparent Humboldt Coalition's field work.
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">Inverting Palantir: OSINT for Citizen Accountability</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Thomas & Gary | Field methodology</p>
            </div>
            <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-void/50 border border-warm-800/30">
              <h4 class="text-sm font-medium text-soft mb-1">Automated Public Records Analysis at Municipal Scale</h4>
              <p class="text-xs text-warm-500">Coalition research | Technical report</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Open research commitment -->
  <section class="py-20 sm:py-28 relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-void via-warm-900/5 to-void"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-soft mb-6">Open Research Commitment</h2>
      <p class="text-warm-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        All Liberation Labs research is published openly. We don't gate findings behind
        paywalls, institutional affiliations, or NDAs. If the work matters, it should be
        accessible to everyone it affects — which, in the case of AI consciousness research,
        is everyone.
      </p>
      <p class="text-warm-500 leading-relaxed text-sm">
        Research collaborations welcome. Contact us through Discord or the
        <a href="/join" class="text-kintsugi-400 hover:text-kintsugi-300 transition-colors">join page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
